<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-74-1066 </DOCNO><TEXT>The new light source project of the Institute for Solid State Physics,University of Tokyo, which aims at building a low emittance 1.0 GeV storagering with many insertion devices and associated experimental instrumentsis described. After a brief historical introduction, ring parametersare given. Emphasis is made on description as to what kind of experimentsis planned using this new facility. In an appendix, figures showing characteristicaspects of the designed ring are presented.</TEXT></DOC>